---
import PolicyPage from '../../components/PolicyPage.astro';
import { getTranslation } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
const title = getTranslation(locale, 'seo.terms.title');
const description = getTranslation(locale, 'seo.terms.description');
const canonicalUrl = '/en/terms';
const updatedAt = '2026-03-09';
---

<PolicyPage
  title={title}
  description={description}
  lang="en"
  canonicalUrl={canonicalUrl}
  pageTitle="Terms and conditions"
  updatedAt={updatedAt}
>
  <section>
    <h2>1. About these terms</h2>
    <p>These terms apply to professional web design and development services provided by Ignacio Amat as a freelance professional.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service provider:</strong> Ignacio Amat</li>
      <li><strong>Contact channel:</strong> the contact form available on this website.</li>
      <li><strong>Location:</strong> Barcelona, Spain</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Scope of services</h2>
    <p>The exact scope of each project is defined in a written proposal, quote or agreement. This website may describe typical services such as landing pages, business websites, redesigns, maintenance, Laravel development or MVP builds, but each engagement is contracted individually.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Quotes and acceptance</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Quotes are indicative until explicitly accepted by both parties.</li>
      <li>Acceptance may occur by email, signature or any other valid written confirmation.</li>
      <li>Changes in scope after acceptance may require updated pricing and timeline estimates.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>4. Working process</h2>
    <p>A project may include definition, structure, design, development, review and launch phases. In order to keep delivery moving, the client is expected to provide feedback, materials and approvals within reasonable timeframes.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>5. Payments</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Unless otherwise agreed, projects may be split into one or more payment milestones.</li>
      <li>Many projects are handled with an initial deposit and a final payment before delivery or launch.</li>
      <li>Amounts are stated in the relevant quote and, unless expressly indicated, do not include applicable taxes.</li>
      <li>Late payments may temporarily pause work or delivery until the outstanding balance is resolved.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>6. Revisions and changes</h2>
    <p>Included revisions are those specifically described in the proposal. Substantial changes outside the original scope may be quoted separately.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>7. Delivery and timelines</h2>
    <p>Timelines are reasonable estimates based on the information and assets available at the time. They may be affected by delayed approvals, scope changes, third-party dependencies or circumstances outside direct control.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>8. Intellectual property and portfolio use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Once agreed payments have been made, the client receives the usage rights for the deliverables included in that project.</li>
      <li>Unless confidentiality obligations or written restrictions apply, the professional may display the completed work in a portfolio or case-study format.</li>
      <li>Third-party licenses, premium resources, fonts, images or external services may require separate purchase or licensing by the client.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>9. Warranty and support</h2>
    <p>After delivery, technical issues directly related to the agreed scope may be corrected during the support period, if any, defined for that project. New change requests, misuse, third-party modifications and issues caused by external providers are excluded.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>Unless mandatory law states otherwise, total liability for a specific project shall not exceed the amount actually paid for that project. No liability is accepted for indirect loss, loss of profit or business decisions taken by the client.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>11. Governing law</h2>
    <p>These terms are governed by Spanish law. Any dispute shall be submitted to the courts of Barcelona unless mandatory law provides another forum.</p>
  </section>
</PolicyPage>
